{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SaP92gmz4UjEgy9fy12hM6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→name: add-field\n     2→description: Add a field to a Django model and propagate to admin, serializer, and factory\n     3→\n     4→variables:\n     5→  model_name:\n     6→    type: string\n     7→    required: true\n     8→    description: \"Name of the model class\"\n     9→  field_name:\n    10→    type: string\n    11→    required: true\n    12→    description: \"Name of the new field\"\n    13→  field_type:\n    14→    type: string\n    15→    required: true\n    16→    description: \"Django field type (e.g., CharField)\"\n    17→  field_args:\n    18→    type: string\n    19→    required: false\n    20→    default: \"\"\n    21→    description: \"Field arguments (e.g., max_length=20, default='bronze')\"\n    22→  factory_default:\n    23→    type: string\n    24→    required: false\n    25→    default: \"'test'\"\n    26→    description: \"Default value for the factory\"\n    27→\n    28→files:\n    29→  - template: templates/model_field.j2\n    30→    patch: \"models.py\"\n    31→    anchor:\n    32→      pattern: \"^class {{ model_name }}\"\n    33→      scope: class_body\n    34→      position: after_last_field\n    35→    skip_if: \"{{ field_name }}\"\n    36→\n    37→  - template: templates/admin_field.j2\n    38→    inject: \"admin.py\"\n    39→    after: 'list_display = \\['\n    40→    skip_if: \"{{ field_name }}\"\n    41→\n    42→  - template: templates/serializer_field.j2\n    43→    inject: \"serializers.py\"\n    44→    after: 'fields = \\['\n    45→    skip_if: \"{{ field_name }}\"\n    46→\n    47→  - template: templates/factory_field.j2\n    48→    patch: \"factories.py\"\n    49→    anchor:\n    50→      pattern: \"^class {{ model_name }}Factory\"\n    51→      scope: class_body\n    52→      position: after_last_field\n    53→    skip_if: \"{{ field_name }}\"\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b24154b-1e80-4ab5-a947-674298697413","uuid":"b623c979-a1df-483c-8568-14b9a2b6723b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KasTrDLCYxLxkJzDUCXjx2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from django.db import models\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→class Reservation(models.Model):\n     5→    guest_name = models.CharField(max_length=100)\n     6→    room_number = models.IntegerField()\n     7→    check_in = models.DateTimeField()\n     8→    check_out = models.DateTimeField()\n     9→    status = models.CharField(max_length=20, default=\"pending\")\n    10→\n    11→    class Meta:\n    12→        ordering = [\"-check_in\"]\n    13→\n    14→    def __str__(self):\n    15→        return f\"{self.guest_name} - Room {self.room_number}\"\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b24154b-1e80-4ab5-a947-674298697413","uuid":"ca2ad84e-c1f3-4820-8468-438c97c5eee5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CDWGBXiZJApZe9CkoJPMP1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from django.contrib import admin\n     2→from .models import Reservation\n     3→\n     4→\n     5→@admin.register(Reservation)\n     6→class ReservationAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):\n     7→    list_display = [\n     8→        \"guest_name\",\n     9→        \"room_number\",\n    10→        \"check_in\",\n    11→        \"check_out\",\n    12→        \"status\",\n    13→    ]\n    14→    list_filter = [\"status\", \"check_in\"]\n    15→    search_fields = [\"guest_name\"]\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b24154b-1e80-4ab5-a947-674298697413","uuid":"40af1a1a-c4ec-421e-80a1-ecd5411dd232"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ao39Mqh4E7S8GhvyPrYh98","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→from rest_framework import serializers\n     2→from .models import Reservation\n     3→\n     4→\n     5→class ReservationSerializer(serializers.ModelSerializer):\n     6→    class Meta:\n     7→        model = Reservation\n     8→        fields = [\n     9→            \"id\",\n    10→            \"guest_name\",\n    11→            \"room_number\",\n    12→            \"check_in\",\n    13→            \"check_out\",\n    14→            \"status\",\n    15→        ]\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7b24154b-1e80-4ab5-a947-674298697413","uuid":"8d849d4b-fdda-4ab2-868d-a19a287f02b4"}
